            {
              "role": "ai",
              "text": "Here's the core concept in pseudocode:\n```\nfunction neuron(inputs, weights) {\n  sum = 0\n  for i in inputs:\n    sum += inputs[i] * weights[i]\n  return activation_function(sum)  // like sigmoid or ReLU\n}\n```\n\nThe breakthrough is that the network adjusts these weights automatically through backpropagation. Each mistake teaches it to get better. Does this demystify the basic building block?"
